   <text>
      <body>
         <head>To <persName><ref target="/persons/pers0000.xml"/>an Unidentified Man</persName><note
               place="foot" n="1">The letter was likely directed to <persName><ref
                     target="/persons/pers0923.xml"/>John Hampson</persName> or one of
                     <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2180.xml"/>JW</persName>&apos;s other
               preachers stationed in <placeName>Leeds</placeName>.</note></head>
         <opener><placeName>London</placeName><lb/><date when="1759-12-09">December 9, 1758</date><lb/><lb/>
            <salute>My Dear Brother,</salute>
         </opener>
         <p>From time to time I have had more trouble with the society at
               <placeName>Leeds</placeName> than with all the other societies in
               <placeName>Yorkshire</placeName>. And now I hear that <hi rend="italic">the
               leaders</hi><!-- I am unsure who the leaders is referencing to and if there is any special tagging I should do for them. -->
            insist that such and such persons be put out of the society! I desire the leaders may
            know their place and not stretch themselves beyond their line. Pray let me judge who
            should be put out of a Methodist society and who not. I desire <persName><ref
                  target="/persons/pers0933.xml"/>Faith</persName> and <persName><ref
                  target="/persons/pers0932.xml"/>Ann Hardwick</persName> may not be put out of the
            society, unless some fresh matter appear against them; and if any new matter does
            appear, let it be laid before <hi rend="italic">me</hi>.</p>
         <p><index indexName="biblical">
               <term cRef="James2:13">He shall have judgement without mercy who hath shown no
                  mercy</term>
            </index>!<note place="foot" n="2">See <index indexName="biblical">
                  <term cRef="James2:13">James 2:13</term>
               </index>.</note> I am,</p>
         <closer><signed>Your affectionate brother,<lb/><persName>J.
            Wesley</persName></signed></closer>
      </body>
